cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of learning distributions of sums of independent random variables with sparse collective support. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in terms of algorithmic results and lower bounds.
